        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Make ChatGPT image generation easy for MCP agents",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add an agent-focused `chatgpt_image` MCP tool backed by Oracle's ChatGPT browser image path.\n- Add image output support to `consult`, returning typed local `artifacts` and `images` metadata.\n- Preserve contributor implementation and credit while merging current `main` and hardening the public contract.\n\n## Maintainer rewrite\n\n- Restrict MCP image writes to `ORACLE_HOME_DIR/generated` by default; explicit `ORACLE_MCP_ALLOW_EXTERNAL_OUTPUT=1` remains the operator opt-in for external paths.\n- Reject traversal, escaping symlinks, dangling symlinks, Oracle config/session/browser-profile paths, and the generated directory itself as a file target.\n- Fail closed for API-engine and remote-browser image output, including dry runs.\n- Omit signed source/download URLs from structured MCP output; return local path, MIME type, size, dimensions, and file ID only.\n- Preserve error output shape, reject known non-ChatGPT model families in `chatgpt_image`, and avoid sessionless image filename collisions.\n- Update MCP/browser docs and changelog; changelog credits @umutkeltek.\n\nMaintainer commits: `7dcad16e`, `34f9e9b9`, `b17aefa3`, `ea6fd28d`.\n\n## Authenticated live proof\n\nReal `chatgpt_image` MCP call through the existing signed-in Chrome profile:\n\n- Session: `pr229-native-image-proof`\n- Model: `gpt-5.5-instant`\n- Status: completed\n- Local artifact: `~/.oracle/generated/pr229-native-image-proof-20260611.png`\n- PNG: 1254 x 1254, 786,988 bytes\n- SHA-256: `a7ec5e6bd77fc1a28a6d2e61206176ad8a6bb580a11f22579218eaffdbb2aec9`\n- Structured response returned `images[]` and `artifacts[]` with local metadata; no signed URLs were exposed.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm check`\n- `pnpm test`: 1,213 passed, 41 skipped\n- `pnpm docs:check`\n- `pnpm docs:site`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm test:packed-cli`\n- `pnpm test:mcp`\n- `$autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n",
